{"word":"κακίζω","slug":"κακίζω","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>κακίζω</b></el> <el>(κᾰκίζω,) </el><br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><a href='S:κακός'><el>κακός</el></a>\n<p/><div class='li500'><b>I. </b><i>to abuse, reproach, accuse</i>, <b><a href='S:Herodotus'>Hdt.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Thucydides'>Thuc.</a></b>, <a href='S:et cetera'>etc.</a><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>II. </b><i>to make cowardly</i>, <b><a href='S:Euripides'>Eur.</a></b>:— <a href='S:passive signification'><a href='S:Passive Voice'>Pass.</a></a> <i>to play the coward</i>, <b><a href='S:Iliad'>Il.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Euripides'>Eur.</a></b>; <el>κακίζεσθαι τύχῃ</el> <i>to be worsted</i> by fortune <i>alone</i>, <b><a href='S:Thucydides'>Thuc.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}